title: Google\Cloud\AIPlatform\V1\ExportModelRequest\OutputConfig
name: OutputConfig
description:
Output configuration for the Model export.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.ExportModelRequest.OutputConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.export_format_id
params.description: The ID of the format in which the Model must be exported. Each Model lists the [export formats it supports][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.Model.supported_export_formats]. If no value is provided here, then the first from the list of the Model's supported formats is used by default.

params.name: data.artifact_destination
params.description: The Cloud Storage location where the Model artifact is to be written to. Under the directory given as the destination a new one with name "model-export-<model-display-name>-<timestamp-of-export-call>", where timestamp is in YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sssZ ISO-8601 format, will be created. Inside, the Model and any of its supporting files will be written. This field should only be set when the exportableContent field of the [Model.supported_export_formats] object contains ARTIFACT.

params.name: data.image_destination
params.description: The Google Container Registry or Artifact Registry uri where the Model container image will be copied to. This field should only be set when the exportableContent field of the [Model.supported_export_formats] object contains IMAGE.
